  "text": "Prometheus enforces TLS and authentication for remote write endpoints through a multi-layered validation approach:\n\n## Configuration Validation\n\n**config/config.go** contains the primary validation logic for remote write configuration:\n- **RemoteWriteConfig** (line 1418): Struct defining remote write endpoint configuration including HTTPClientConfig, SigV4Config, AzureADConfig, and GoogleIAMConfig\n- **RemoteWriteConfig.UnmarshalYAML** (line 1447-1478): Unmarshals and validates remote write YAML config, calling HTTPClientConfig.Validate() to validate TLS settings and validateAuthConfigs() to ensure at most one authentication method is configured\n- **validateAuthConfigs** (line 1490-1515): Validates that at most one of basic_auth, authorization, oauth2, sigv4, azuread, or google_iam is configured for remote write\n- **validateHeaders** (line 1529-1539): Validates that authorization headers are not manually configured\n\n## Bearer Token and Basic Auth Handling\n\nBoth Bearer tokens and basic auth are enforced through the HTTPClientConfig from prometheus/common library. The validation ensures:\n- Bearer tokens and Bearer token files cannot be used simultaneously\n- Basic auth and Bearer tokens cannot be used together\n- Authorization headers cannot override these configured authentication methods\n\n## HTTP Client Creation and TLS Enforcement\n\n**storage/remote/client.go**:\n- **NewWriteClient** (line 182-238): Creates HTTP client for remote write using config_util.NewClientFromConfig, which validates and applies TLS configuration from HTTPClientConfig\n- **NewReadClient** (line 150-180): Similarly creates HTTP client for remote read\n\nThe HTTP client creation applies all TLS and authentication configuration through:\n- TLS certificate and key validation (paired validation)\n- Bearer token handling\n- Basic auth configuration\n- OAuth2 and SigV4 configuration\n\n## Remote Write Configuration Application\n\n**storage/remote/write.go**:\n- **WriteStorage.ApplyConfig** (line 140-220): Applies remote write configuration to create write clients, passing HTTPClientConfig, SigV4Config, AzureADConfig, and GoogleIAMConfig to NewWriteClient\n\n## Azure AD Authentication\n\n**storage/remote/azuread/azuread.go**:\n- **AzureADConfig** (line 90-109): Configuration struct for Azure AD authentication\n- **AzureADConfig.Validate** (line 130-224): Validates Azure AD config including cloud selection, authentication method selection (ManagedIdentity, WorkloadIdentity, OAuth, SDK), and required credentials validation\n- **AzureADConfig.UnmarshalYAML** (line 226-234): Unmarshals and validates Azure AD YAML\n- **NewAzureADRoundTripper** (line 236-251): Creates HTTP round tripper that attaches Azure AD Bearer tokens to remote write requests\n\n## Google IAM Authentication\n\n**storage/remote/googleiam/googleiam.go**:\n- **NewRoundTripper** (line 32-54): Creates HTTP round tripper that attaches Google Cloud OAuth2 access tokens to remote write requests using service account credentials\n\n## Configuration Validation Tools\n\n**cmd/promtool/main.go**:\n- **checkTLSConfig** (line 790-810): Validates TLS configuration, ensuring cert and key files are paired and exist\n- **checkConfig** (line 663-750): Validates entire Prometheus configuration including remote write settings through config.LoadFile() which triggers all validation during YAML unmarshaling\n\n## Validation Flow\n\nThe complete validation chain for remote write TLS and authentication:\n1. Configuration file is loaded via config.LoadFile()\n2. RemoteWriteConfig.UnmarshalYAML is called for each remote_write section\n3. HTTPClientConfig.Validate() checks TLS files are properly paired and present\n4. validateAuthConfigs() ensures at most one authentication method is configured\n5. For Azure AD configs, AzureADConfig.Validate() is called during UnmarshalYAML\n6. WriteStorage.ApplyConfig creates write clients with validated configuration\n7. NewWriteClient creates HTTP client applying all TLS and auth configuration\n8. Round trippers for Azure AD and Google IAM are applied if configured\n\nThis multi-layered approach ensures that remote write endpoints enforce proper TLS and authentication configuration at configuration load time, preventing insecure remote write configurations from being deployed."
}

